      "comment": "JILLIBY TOPGUN (3) has been excellent of late and made it two wins in a row when successful at his latest appearance at Shepparton, getting home by 1.3 metres. Stays in the same grade and should enjoy an economical run from this draw. Can land the hat trick. FREMARKS PEGGY (8) has been knocking on the door and made it back-to-back placings when third from this row last start at Maryborough. Usually races well here and draws for a nice trail. Could break through. JETAWAY SAINT (7) hasn't raced for six months but was readied with a trial win. Proven fresh so expect a good effort to kick off this prep. MIDNITE MUSCLE (4) suffered interference and broke last start but had been runner-up from the back row in the previous two outings so is worth another chance.",
